{
  "explanation": "The defendant abused a position of professional trust as an accountant to misappropriate $25,000. While embezzlement is a serious breach of fiduciary duty and requires a period of incarceration to satisfy the goals of deterrence and justice, several mitigating factors were considered: the defendant has no prior criminal history and has demonstrated remorse and a commitment to restitution by partially paying back the stolen funds. Based on these factors, a sentence of 12 months is appropriate.",
  "verdict": 12
}
